ed like a tight comma, second like a diagonal slash, third like a larger comma, final like a downwards slash).",{"_":50,"ana":51,"ref":52},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":54,"dimensions":55},"Letters are tall and precise. There are simple, but standard, serifs on all letters. P is very open, T and L have wavy cross bars.",[56,62,66,70],{"type":57,"l":58,"from":59,"to":59,"h":60,"unit":61},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","39-40","mm",{"type":57,"l":63,"from":64,"to":64,"h":65,"unit":61},"Line 2","line2","39-41",{"type":57,"l":67,"from":68,"to":68,"h":69,"unit":61},"Line 3","line3","39-44",{"type":71,"l":72,"from":59,"to":64,"unit":61},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2",{"_":74,"notBefore":75,"notAfter":76,"evidence":77},"later 2nd century CE (Ferrua on the basis of the letter forms)",150,200,"lettering",[79,84],{"_":80,"type":81,"ref":82,"cert":83},"Thermae Himeraeae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462513","low",{"_":85,"type":86,"ref":87},"Termini Imerese","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/6539140",[89],[90,91],37.98365,13.69555,{"_":93,"type":94,"subtype":95,"notAfter":96,"geo":20},"First recorded/seen by Ferrua in 1941 in the museum, provenance assumed to be Termini Imerese.","found","discovered","1941",{"_":98,"type":99,"subtype":100,"when":101,"resp":102,"geo":20},"Antoniou, 2023-07-05. In the Depositi of Museo Civico Baldassare Romano, room 1, scaffold 8, shelf 1","observed","autopsied","2023-07-05","#AA",[104,111],{"n":105,"url":106,"height":107,"width":108,"desc":109,"surfaceType":110},"screen","ISic000157_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-05.","front",{"n":105,"url":112,"height":107,"width":108,"desc":109,"surfaceType":113},"ISic000157_rear_tiled.tif","rear","Italy","Sicily",{"_":117,"role":118,"ref":119,"museum":120},"Museo Civico Baldassare Romano","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/066",{"slug":121,"type":118,"name":117,"uri":119,"description":122,"location":123},"066","A large and well-displayed collection. It begins with three ante-rooms, in the first of which is a rich display of lithics (mainly Neolithic) from the surrounding area. A display of material from Himera (lion-head spouts from the Temple of Victory and red-figure craters being the principle pieces) and a numismatic gallery then follow before the main room which contains Hellenistic and Roman material from Termini Imerese itself. Small finds, sculpture and inscriptions predominate. The museum collection continues upstairs with non-archaeological material (and a single inscription). The courtyard of the building holds a large collection of architectural pieces and inscriptions",{"settlement":85,"region":124,"country":114,"address":125,"geo":126},"Palermo","Via Marco Tullio Cicerone, 90018 - Termini Imerese (PA)",{"lat":127,"lon":128},37.98655109,13.69587845,{"_":130,"type":131},"68","inventory",{"_":133,"mainLang":134,"languages":135},"Latin","la",[133],{"type":137,"bibl":138},"edition",[139,147,151,159],{"type":140,"n":141,"citedRange":142,"ptr":143,"ref":145},"bulletin","AE","1994.0777",{"target":144},"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/R46KDTZX",{"_":146,"target":146},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283",{"type":140,"n":141,"citedRange":148,"ptr":149,"ref":150},"1977.0339",{"target":144},{"_":146,"target":146},{"type":152,"n":153,"citedRange":154,"ptr":155,"ref":157},"corpus","ILMusTermini","78",{"target":156},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/JCV85C79",{"_":158,"target":158},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137",{"author":160,"date":96,"citedRange":161,"ptr":162,"ref":164},"Ferrua","262 no.22",{"target":163},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/P7QQ9SB6",{"_":165,"target":165},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002655",{"type":16