mbers of the gens Coponia from Thermae Himeraeae, see \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000156\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000156\u003C/a> and \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000158\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000158\u003C/a>, and another attestation from Messana, see \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000273\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000273\u003C/a>. As Bivona (1994) stresses, the gens Coponia is represented by a handful of republican senators and one equestrian procurator of Judaea under Augustus.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":242,"html":243},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 1994.0777 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 1977.0339 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 78 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ferrua 1941 262 no.22 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002655\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002655\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":245,"html":246},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[248,251],{"id":249,"lang":134,"html":250},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"dis\">d(is)\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"manibus\">m(anibus)\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=