>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"TA\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8417-7089\">Tuuli Ahlholm\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>EpiDoc editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n\t    \u003CrespStmt>\n     \t       \u003Cname xml:id=\"SS\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569\">Simona Stoyanova\u003C/name>\n     \t       \u003Cresp>standardisation of template and tidying up encoding\u003C/resp>\n \t   \u003C/respStmt>\n\t    \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"system\">system\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>automated or batch processes\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"AA\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>Epidoc editing and addition of metadata\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n            \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic000157\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\">175735\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\">076863\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\">10900650\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000157\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"DOI\" when=\"2020-12-17\">10.5281/zenodo.4334360\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Termini Imerese\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"museum\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/066\">Museo Civico Baldassare Romano\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">68\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003C!--Pencil 714 on front, red 42 on front-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"la\">Latin\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>Large rectangular plaque in brown/grey marble. Lower left corner missing, obscuring the beginning of lines 2-3. Traces of likely modern mortar and paint on sides. Stone is polished smooth on front face, but is not uniformly flat on the front surface. Rear is almost perfectly flat and polished.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.marble\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html\">marble\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.plaque\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html\">plaque\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">23.5\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">36.5\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">3\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Three lines of Latin text, centred on the stone, with the header of line 1 filling the upper half of the stone. Interpuncts only used in final line, and do not follow a consistent pattern (first visible interpunct is shaped like a tight comma, second like a diagonal slash, third like a larger comma, final like a downwards slash).\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Letters are tall and precise. There are simple, but standard, serifs on all letters. P is very open, T and L have wavy cross bars.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\">39-40\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line2\" to=\"line2\">Line 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\">39-41\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line3\" to=\"line3\">Line 3\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\">39-44\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462513\" cert=\"low\">Thermae Himeraeae\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/6539140\">Termini Imerese\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.98365, 13.69555\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0150\" notAfter-custom=\"0200\" evidence=\"lettering\">later 2nd century CE (Ferrua on the basis of the letter forms)\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" notAfter=\"1941\">First recorded/seen by Ferrua in 1941 in the museum, provenance assumed to be Termini Imerese.\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\" when=\"2023-07-05\" resp=\"#AA\">Antoniou, 2023-07-05. In the Depositi of Museo Civico Baldassare Romano, room 1, scaffold 8, shelf 1\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded followi